# AhaDiff

Use AhaDiff after meaningful code changes to produce verified learn-back
artifacts for the current diff.

- Run `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD` for the latest commit.
- Run `ahadiff learn --staged` before committing staged work.
- Run `ahadiff quiz <run_id>` and `ahadiff review` for retention.
- Prefer `ahadiff verify <run_id>` when reviewing existing artifacts.
- Use `ahadiff improve <run_id>` for targeted follow-up and `ahadiff serve` for
  local WebUI inspection.
- Keep provider credentials in environment variables.
- Treat `.ahadiff/review.sqlite`, `.ahadiff/runs/`, and `prompts/` as local
  AhaDiff state unless the repository policy says otherwise.
- Do not commit `.ahadiff/audit.private.jsonl` or local provider endpoints.
